alert.note: Alert for Central Aleutians (Alaska) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 09 at 5:11AM AKST until February 09 at 7:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM AKST THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Northeast winds 35 to 55 mph with gusts up to 75 mph expected. * WHERE...Central Aleutians. * WHEN...Until 7 PM AKST this evening. * IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property, and cause power outages. Travel will be difficult. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Peak winds are expected later this morning through the early afternoon. With temperatures expected to stay at or above freezing, significant visibility reductions due to blowing snow are unlikely. Wet snow should transition to a rain/snow mix or rain by early afternoon.
info.instruction: People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown around or damaged by the wind. Prepare for the possibility of widespread power outages. Use caution if you must travel.
